{
  "_comment": [
    "Canonical brand token list for iRECON hostname-level brand detection.",
    "Every entry is a lowercase string that will be matched EXACTLY against",
    "individual hostname tokens produced by splitting labels on '.', '-', '_'.",
    "",
    "Rules for inclusion:",
    "  1. Must be a real, recognisable brand name — not a generic word.",
    "  2. Must be distinctive enough that an exact match on a hostname token",
    "     is meaningful.  Short generic words (e.g. 'mail', 'web', 'app')",
    "     are excluded to keep false-positive rates low.",
    "  3. Brands are grouped by sector for maintainability.",
    "  4. Multi-word brand names that commonly appear hyphenated in hostnames",
    "     appear as their hyphen-split tokens (e.g. 'wellsfargo' as one token,",
    "     but 'bankofamerica' is unlikely to appear split so stays compound).",
    "",
    "Do NOT add generic infrastructure words: login, secure, update, support,",
    "portal, account, verify, confirm, signin, auth, access, online, service."
  ],
